Description: Shoulder fragment of North Ionian Late Wild Goat pottery oinochoe, black-figured; interior reserved; exterior, cream slip: part of a swan to left with zone of solid tongues above and thick band of dark brown and red stripes below; filling ornaments: rosettes, half rosettes and dots; red patches on swan and every third tongue; incision used for details of swan.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir William Matthew Flinders Petrie
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Ashmolean Museum, Oxford. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.

Published in CVA Oxford 2, II D, p. 80, no. 33, pl. IV.33, which gives 1925.608d as the inventory number. Certainly the piece was not originally registered as 1925.608e, as it differs from the kind of wares described in the Ashmolean Museum register as belonging to this registration sequence, even if 1928.608e is the number it now bears.
